Ontario's open power market: How the key players are players are positioning themselves 
  
(Our apologies if you receive multiple copies of this message. Several lists were combined to ensure complete coverage) 
  
Ontario's power market is set to open to competition by May of 2002. Every consumer, trader, distributor, producer and regulator of power is actively preparing plans to make the most of the new situation. Nearly $10 billion worth of annual sales are "up for grabs." Take advantage of this exceptional lineup of experts to fully compare your options before the best opportunities are spoken for: 
Hear the top business leaders and decision-makers in the electricity business explain their latest plans and reasoning for engaging themselves in the Ontario electricity market: 
Ontario's Minister of Finance and Deputy Premier Jim Flaherty 
TransAlta's CEO Steve Snyder 
Ontario's Minister of Energy Jim Wilson 
Chair of Bruce Power, Robin Jeffrey 
The CEO of Toronto Hydro, Courtney Pratt 
Ontario's Minister of Environment, Elizabeth Witmer 
Senior authorities from the grid operators in Pennsylvania, California and Ontario 
Question dozens of the most relevant authorities in the business on how the Ontario market will evolve in the first phases of development. (See attached text file for program details or download the full brochure online at http://www.newenergy.org/conference.html ) 
Tour the Trade Show and see what the suppliers and most active entrepreneurs in the business will be bringing out next year. 
The 2001 Canadian Independent Power Conference and Trade Show is being co-presented by the Canadian Electricity Association and in co-ordination with the Green Power Trade Show, ensuring a diverse and lively interchange of perspectives. The Ontario Ministry of Environment will be offering a one-time only workshop on their new emission regulations at the same venue. Now in our 13th year, the organizers are expecting over 600 delegates and 90 Trade Show exhibitors. 
This is truly the single most effective opportunity to gain a complete and timely perspective on where the market is going and what you can do to make the most of it! 
I have attached the complete Conference program for your review. You can register using the form on the last page of the Conference brochure available on our web site http://www.newenergy.org/conference.html   (print it out and fax back to out office at 416-481-5785) or by calling our office at 416-322-6549. 
Thank you for considering this unique opportunity. Please feel free to contact me for further information. I hope to meet you at our Conference. 
Sincerely, 
Mike Coughlan 
Marketing Manager 
 

